          <source>A <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Menu&gt;</ph> is a control that allows hierarchical organization of elements associated with commands or event handlers.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Each <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Menu&gt;</ph> can contain multiple <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem&gt;</ph> controls.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Each <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem&gt;</ph> can invoke a command or invoke a <ph id="ph2">`Click`</ph> event handler.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>A <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem&gt;</ph> can also have multiple <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem&gt;</ph> elements as children, forming a submenu.</source>
